events.name: Indiana Pacers at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: - Tyrese Haliburton scored 16 of his 28 points in a dazzling 2-1/2 minute display late in the third quarter, Pascal Siakam scored 23 and the Indiana Pacers downed Victor Wembanyama and the San Antonio Spurs 136-98 in the NBA Paris Games finale on...
headlines.shortLinkText: Haliburton scores 28, Pacers run away from Wembanyama and Spurs in 136-98 win in Paris

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 34 points and became the Minnesota Timberwolves' career leader in 3-pointers in a 133-104 victory over the Denver Nuggets 133-104 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards scores 34, sets Timberwolves career 3-pointer record in 133-104 win over Denver

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 24 points, Derrick White added 23, including Boston’s first 11 of the third quarter, and the Celtics beat the Dallas Mavericks 122-107 on Saturday night in the first meeting between the teams since the NBA Finals.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum, White help Celtics pull away to beat Mavericks 122-107 in first meeting since NBA Finals

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro scored 25 points, Bam Adebayo had 17 points and 16 rebounds, and the Miami Heat beat the Brooklyn Nets 106-97 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Herro, Adebayo lead Heat past Nets 106-97 on Vince Carter's jersey retirement night

highlights.description: Vince Carter's No. 15 is hung in the rafters after his jersey is officially retired on Saturday night by the Nets.

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Charlotte Hornets

headlines.description: — LaMelo Ball scored 25 points, Miles Bridges had 22 and the Charlotte Hornets beat the New Orleans Pelicans 123-92 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaMelo Ball scores 25 points to help the Hornets beat the Pelicans, 123-92

headlines.description: — Franz Wagner scored 25 of his 32 points in the fourth quarter, Paolo Banchero had 32 points, nine rebounds and seven assists, and the Orlando Magic beat the Detroit Pistons 121-113 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wagner, Banchero score 32 points each in Magic's 121-113 win over Pistons

headlines.description: — Scottie Barnes had 24 points and 11 rebounds and the Toronto Raptors swept a two-game set in Atlanta for their season-high third straight victory, beating the Hawks 117-94 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Raptors sweep 2-game set in Atlanta, beating the Hawks 117-94

headlines.description: — Amen Thompson had his second career triple-double, Alperin Sengun and Jalen Green scored 26 points apiece and the Houston Rockets beat the Eastern Conference-leading Cleveland Cavaliers 135-131 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thompson has triple-double as Rockets beat East-leading Cavaliers for second time in week, 135-131

events.name: Sacramento Kings at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — OG Anunoby scored 33 points, Josh Hart added 20 points, 18 rebounds and 11 assists in his sixth triple-double of the season and the New York Knicks beat the Sacramento Kings 143-120 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks get four 20-point scorers, another triple-double from Hart in 143-120 victory over Kings

headlines.description: — Tyrese Maxey had 31 points and nine assists, Kelly Oubre Jr. added 22 points and 12 rebounds and the Philadelphia 76ers beat the Chicago Bulls 109-97 on Saturday night for their second straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tyrese Maxey has 31 points and 9 assists in the 76ers' 109-97 victory over the Bulls

headlines.description: — Jaren Jackson Jr. scored 28 points, Zach Edey added 19 points and four blocks and the Memphis Grizzlies won their sixth straight by beating the Utah Jazz 125-103 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jaren Jackson scores 28, Zach Edey adds 19 and Grizzlies win 6th straight, 125-103 over Jazz

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis had 36 points and 13 rebounds, LeBron James added 25 points and 12 assists, and the Los Angeles Lakers beat the Golden State Warriors 118-108 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Davis, James lead Lakers to 118-108 victory over Warriors as Curry goes scoreless in second half

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant scored 29 points, Nick Richards added 20 points along with a career-high 19 rebounds and the Phoenix Suns held off the Washington Wizards 119-109 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant scores 29 points as the Suns hand the Wizards their 13th straight loss, 119-109

headlines.description: — James Harden scored 40 points and the Los Angeles Clippers overcame Giannis Antetokounmpo and Damian Lillard to beat the Milwaukee Bucks 127-117 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden scores 40 points to lead Clippers over Bucks 127-117, snapping Milwaukee's 5-game win streak
